sudo apt install git :- To Install Git 

git --version :- To Check Version of Git

git config --global user.name "Username" :- To Set Username (GitHub)

git config --global user.email "Email" :- To Set Email (GitHub)

git config --list :- To List/View the Username & Email 

git init :- To Initialize Git in a Folder 

git config --global init.defaultBranch <branch name> :- To Change the Name of Default Master Branch

git remote add origin <Link> :- To Connect Local Repository to GitHub Remote Repository

git clone <Link> : To Clone Repository into Local Machine 

git remote set-url origin https://<token>@github.com/<username>/<repo> :- To Use the Personal Access Token For a Repo

git status :- To Track/Check the Status of Untracked File 

git add <filename> :- To Track the File

git add . :- To Track All Files 

git commit -m "Message" :- To Commit the Changes 

git push origin master/main :- To Push the Local Changes to GitHub

git push -u orign master/main :- Sets up Upstream Branch for Current Local Directory 

git pull origin master : To Fetch the Latest Changes

git checkout -b main origin/main :- Used to Create a New local branch main , Switch to it to make it Current Branch & Set it to Track origin/main that is the branch in remote repository 

git checkout :- Used to Switch Branches

-b <branch name> :- Create New Branch 

origin/main :- origin is the default name for Remote Repository , main is the branch in Remote Repository & this says Local Branch should Track it

git branch -M <branch name> :- Rename the Cirrent Branch 

git branch :- To check all the branches & marks * to the Current Branch

git push origin --delete <branch name> :- To Delete the Branch

git remote -v :- To List all the Configured Local Directory

git remote remove origin :- To Remove Existing Origin



